1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,074
Initial framework by AB69
<font color="#800000">Transcript overhaul & sync by The_Turbaned_Sun</font>

2
00:00:55,500 --> 00:01:02,195
50 years ago, an alien force known
as the Formics attacked Earth.

3
00:01:02,507 --> 00:01:04,293
10 millions died.

4
00:01:06,013 --> 00:01:08,303
It was only through the sacrifice of our greatest commander

5
00:01:08,303 --> 00:01:11,549
that we avoided total annihilation.

6
00:01:25,157 --> 00:01:29,489
We've been preparing for them to come back,
ever since.

7
00:01:29,489 --> 00:01:31,240
The International Fleet decided

8
00:01:31,443 --> 00:01:34,689
that the world's smartest children
are the planet's best hope.

9
00:01:34,910 --> 00:01:41,297
Raised on war-games, their decisions
are intuitive, decisive, fearless.

10
00:01:41,398 --> 00:01:44,748
I am one of those recruits.

11
00:01:46,079 --> 00:01:47,679
I've watched through his eyes,

12
00:01:47,705 --> 00:01:50,256
I've listened through his ears

13
00:01:51,256 --> 00:01:54,782
and I tell you, he's THE ONE!

14
00:01:54,783 --> 00:01:57,400
That's what you said about his brother.

15
00:01:57,609 --> 00:02:00,041
Brother tested out impossible for other reasons

16
00:02:00,042 --> 00:02:03,043
... nothing to do with his tactical abilities.

17
00:02:03,393 --> 00:02:05,871
- I gotcha! I gotcha!
- Try there... go back!

18
00:02:06,116 --> 00:02:09,047
He's gonna crush 'em.

19
00:02:10,828 --> 00:02:13,063
God!!

20
00:02:13,376 --> 00:02:15,878
- You can't do that.
- You've got to use what is around you.

21
00:02:15,879 --> 00:02:17,798
No no,
I had you all the way through the belt!

22
00:02:17,799 --> 00:02:21,011
You might have calculated your trajectory
wrong due to the incoming asteroids.

23
00:02:21,012 --> 00:02:23,450
Don't.. lecture me. Wiggin.
You cheated!

24
00:02:25,073 --> 00:02:27,377
It was a good game...

25
00:02:28,109 --> 00:02:30,029
Thanks.

26
00:02:32,561 --> 00:02:34,273
HEY!

27
00:02:39,105 --> 00:02:40,723
Play again!

28
00:02:40,924 --> 00:02:41,698
Sorry.

29
00:02:41,924 --> 00:02:44,215
Tomorrow, maybe?

30
00:02:44,215 --> 00:02:47,191
You see, he's got a talent for strategy.

31
00:02:47,192 --> 00:02:49,182
His humility could be false,

32
00:02:49,183 --> 00:02:53,407
part of a strategy to avoid antagonizing 
an ego-driven opponent.

33
00:02:53,581 --> 00:02:55,256
Which makes him even smarter.

34
00:02:55,256 --> 00:02:57,073
He may be a genius but we need someone

35
00:02:57,074 --> 00:02:59,966
the others will follow . A leader.
He can't win on his own.

36
00:03:00,036 --> 00:03:03,127
Well, let's see how he handles rejection.

37
00:03:04,137 --> 00:03:10,154
Andrew Wiggin! Andrew... Ender Wiggin...
Please report to the infirmary!

38
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:12,946
Ender Wiggin to the infirmary.

39
00:03:20,697 --> 00:03:22,930
- Hello Ender!
- Hello!

40
00:03:22,931 --> 00:03:24,909
That nasty monitor is coming out today.

41
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:27,168
Please, lie face down.

42
00:03:27,691 --> 00:03:30,309
Am I off the program?

43
00:03:30,959 --> 00:03:35,602
- Did I do something wrong?
- That's not really for me to say.

44
00:03:42,897 --> 00:03:44,433
Lie down.

45
00:03:44,459 --> 00:03:47,603
The sooner we get this done,
the sooner you can move on.

46
00:03:59,874 --> 00:04:00,874
Ready?

47
00:04:00,875 --> 00:04:02,692
This won't hurt a bit.

48
00:04:35,855 --> 00:04:39,101
Where do you think you're going, Wiggin?

49
00:04:39,323 --> 00:04:41,382
Washed out, huh?

50
00:04:41,383 --> 00:04:45,547
- Come on!
<i>- Come on! Get him in there!</i>

51
00:04:51,507 --> 00:04:55,172
Come on, chief... one on one,
for real this time.

52
00:04:55,173 --> 00:04:58,976
- No games.
- He's got no monitor now.
- That's right.

53
00:04:58,978 --> 00:05:01,979
No one wants you now, Wiggin.

54
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:08,193
One-on-one,
then why are your boys holding me?

55
00:05:08,554 --> 00:05:10,023
Let's go!

56
00:05:10,048 --> 00:05:12,048
Come on, man!

57
00:05:23,496 --> 00:05:26,662
- Stay down.
- I'm gonna kill you, chief (???)

58
00:05:29,443 --> 00:05:31,317
Take it easy, Ender.

59
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:40,543
You might be thinking of 
ganging up on me...

60
00:05:40,543 --> 00:05:43,884
But just remember what I do to people
who try to hurt me.

61
00:05:57,626 --> 00:05:59,755
He said I was cheating...

62
00:05:59,755 --> 00:06:03,315
he said that was why I was off the program.
And I kept on kicking him...

63
00:06:03,316 --> 00:06:05,968
- Doesn't matter.
- ...even after he was down.

64
00:06:05,969 --> 00:06:09,843
- He will never bully you again.
- All I could think was...

65
00:06:09,844 --> 00:06:12,880
...what would Peter do?

66
00:06:14,765 --> 00:06:18,815
- I'm just like him, now.
- No. No, you're nothing like him Ender.

67
00:06:18,816 --> 00:06:20,410
Nothing like whom?

68
00:06:20,410 --> 00:06:23,028
- I thought you had a game.
- Rained out...

69
00:06:23,098 --> 00:06:25,251
- What's he crying about?
- I'm not crying!

70
00:06:25,565 --> 00:06:28,847
My monitor's gone. Now I'm just like you.

71
00:06:28,882 --> 00:06:32,720
You mean Mom & Dad spent all that money on a Third
and now he's off the program, too?

72
00:06:32,721 --> 00:06:35,338
Stop it, Peter. He made it farther than either of us.

73
00:06:35,339 --> 00:06:39,088
Hey, drop out!
Remember how to play formics and astronauts?

74
00:06:39,088 --> 00:06:42,344
- That's it. Where is mom?
- No. Don't.

75
00:06:42,345 --> 00:06:47,338
- I'll play.
- Put the mask on... you can be the bug.

76
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:52,190
<i>- Peter, you're sick!</i>
- Stay out of this, Valentine.
<i>- No. Stop it.</i>

77
00:06:52,191 --> 00:06:57,530
- Okay bug. You started it. You attack first.
<i>- Let me in.</i>
- Come on...

78
00:06:59,347 --> 00:07:04,245
- Come on, fight back. At last, we've got one of you alive.
<i>- Peter, stop!</i>

79
00:07:04,246 --> 00:07:08,226
You know, I could kill you just like this.

80
00:07:09,330 --> 00:07:12,671
- Please!
- I should've been chosen!

81
00:07:24,446 --> 00:07:28,887
Deep Space intel shows us that the
number of enemy ships already

82
00:07:28,889 --> 00:07:33,366
deployed is 10 times those
we faced during the first invasion.

83
00:07:33,566 --> 00:07:38,781
The Formics are rebuilding and strengthening
their fleet. We must conquer or die.

84
00:07:38,781 --> 00:07:40,246
Turn it off please, John.

85
00:07:40,247 --> 00:07:42,376
Why? You'd rather not know
what's going on in the world?

86
00:07:42,376 --> 00:07:48,604
We must never again bear witness
to the slaughter of tens of millions of innocent people
as we did during the Formic invasion.

87
00:07:48,709 --> 00:07:50,278
I'd rather you talk to your son.

88
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:55,390
Our survival demands total commitment
to the destruction of the enemy...

89
00:07:55,459 --> 00:07:58,706
If you want, I'll go away.
So you don't have to be embarrassed.

90
00:07:58,916 --> 00:08:01,778
Ender, no one is embarrassed.

91
00:08:02,206 --> 00:08:05,627
I am a Third.
I should never have been born.

92
00:08:05,628 --> 00:08:07,912
No. We wanted you, Ender.
We just needed permission.

93
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:16,753
John, please say something.

94
00:08:18,393 --> 00:08:20,697
It's a tough program, Ender.

95
00:08:22,303 --> 00:08:27,028
When they brought me to this country,
there was less competition and still I didn't make it.

96
00:08:27,376 --> 00:08:30,553
You have nothing to be ashamed of...

97
00:08:30,577 --> 00:08:32,322
...nothing.

98
00:08:33,683 --> 00:08:37,662
<i>#Sensor alert! Front door...
Please state your name.#</i>

99
00:08:37,663 --> 00:08:45,482
Colonel Hyrum Graff, Director of Training, International Fleet.
This is my colleague, Major Anderson. May we?

100
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:48,159
Why'd you keep kicking him?
You had already won the fight.

101
00:08:48,161 --> 00:08:50,568
- Did you enjoy it?
- No.

102
00:08:50,568 --> 00:08:53,781
Then why? Speak up, son.

103
00:08:55,805 --> 00:09:00,308
Knocking him down was the first fight.

104
00:09:00,866 --> 00:09:03,216
I wanted to win all the next ones, too.

105
00:09:03,217 --> 00:09:04,927
So they'd leave me alone.

106
00:09:04,928 --> 00:09:07,196
Don't you think you should have
asked a grown up for help?

107
00:09:07,197 --> 00:09:12,712
Nonsense! He can fight his own battles.
Colonel, he was obviously being bullied and he defended himself.

108
00:09:12,713 --> 00:09:14,528
Son...

109
00:09:14,529 --> 00:09:19,484
I'd like to offer you a place in our program.

110
00:09:24,849 --> 00:09:26,630
But you took away my monitor.

111
00:09:26,664 --> 00:09:31,586
The final step in our evaluation is always to
see what happens when the monitor is removed.

112
00:09:31,587 --> 00:09:35,251
And he passed?
He put a child in the hospital.

113
00:09:35,252 --> 00:09:40,862
It's not what he did, it's why he did it.
It was tactical, a strategy to stop future attacks.

114
00:09:40,863 --> 00:09:43,620
Andrew, you don't have to do this.

115
00:09:43,621 --> 00:09:46,831
Ender and I should have
a private conversation.

116
00:09:46,832 --> 00:09:53,535
- Absolutely not.
- With all respect sir, you really can't stop me.

117
00:09:55,174 --> 00:09:58,222
Formics might have wiped us
out the last time, you know.

118
00:10:00,411 --> 00:10:04,983
A brilliant commander is the
only thing that saved us.

119
00:10:04,983 --> 00:10:07,043
Mazer Rackham?

120
00:10:07,463 --> 00:10:11,710
Mazer Rackham!
We need minds like yours, Ender.

121
00:10:11,711 --> 00:10:16,470
Young people integrate complex data more easily than adults.

122
00:10:18,158 --> 00:10:20,496
Will the monitor be reinstalled?

123
00:10:20,497 --> 00:10:21,927
No.

124
00:10:21,928 --> 00:10:24,406
You graduated.

125
00:10:24,406 --> 00:10:27,477
To Battle School.

126
00:10:27,477 --> 00:10:31,875
Privacy rights are restored.

127
00:10:31,946 --> 00:10:40,464
If there's a chance, because of you, the Formics
might leave us alone forever...

128
00:10:40,778 --> 00:10:45,398
then I have to ask you to come with me.

129
00:10:49,447 --> 00:10:52,590
It's what I was born for, right?

130
00:10:55,650 --> 00:10:58,352
Valentine was too compassionate for Battle School.

131
00:11:05,343 --> 00:11:08,671
My brother Peter washed out
because he was too quick to violence.

132
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:15,643
Colonel Graff said I needed to find a balance
between those emotions if I were to succeed.

133
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:24,612
Join the others.

134
00:11:25,521 --> 00:11:27,231
Go on!

135
00:11:42,162 --> 00:11:45,582
- You're late!
- Out of my control.

136
00:11:45,582 --> 00:11:47,573
I'm Ender.

137
00:11:47,992 --> 00:11:52,495
Ender?
What kind of name is that?

138
00:11:52,496 --> 00:11:55,078
What's your name?

139
00:11:55,846 --> 00:11:57,066
Name is Bean.

140
00:11:57,067 --> 00:12:02,094
- Bean?
- Grew up on the streets, not with a bean. (???)

141
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:56,554
- I'm gonna be...
- Bag! Give him the bag!

142
00:13:07,598 --> 00:13:09,797
Close the bag!

143
00:13:12,764 --> 00:13:14,929
- You alright?
- Yeah.

144
00:13:17,756 --> 00:13:19,535
What're you doing, Wiggin?

145
00:13:19,536 --> 00:13:22,608
- Nothing, sir.
- Something funny?

146
00:13:23,341 --> 00:13:25,924
I asked you a question, launchy.

147
00:13:26,797 --> 00:13:31,997
Sir, the way you're floating. Horizontally.
I thought that was funny.

148
00:13:31,998 --> 00:13:33,046
Really, why?

149
00:13:33,139 --> 00:13:36,770
Because in zero gravity, there is no right side up.

150
00:13:36,770 --> 00:13:40,354
You may think you're vertical and we may be horizontal.

151
00:13:40,739 --> 00:13:43,321
- Is that funny?
- Sir, no sir!

152
00:13:44,020 --> 00:13:45,590
Yes, it is.

153
00:13:46,115 --> 00:13:49,151
Alai, you know what he is talking about?

154
00:13:49,151 --> 00:13:51,630
- Yes, sir.
- No, you don't.

155
00:13:52,013 --> 00:13:57,039
There's only one kid on this launch
with any brains at all so far...

156
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:59,131
...and that's Ender Wiggin.

157
00:14:36,990 --> 00:14:41,990
<i>#All new arrivals follow the yellow lights
to your accommodation. The yellow lights.#</i>

158
00:14:48,415 --> 00:14:53,415
<i>#All new arrivals follow the yellow lights
to your accommodation. The yellow lights.#</i>

159
00:14:53,956 --> 00:14:55,596
So you made them hate me.

160
00:14:55,596 --> 00:14:57,655
I told them you were the best.

161
00:14:57,656 --> 00:15:00,343
We need a Julius Caesar, a Napoleon.

162
00:15:00,344 --> 00:15:01,669
We hope that would be you.

163
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:06,349
- Caesar was assassinated by the people he trusted.
- Napoleon lost in the end.

164
00:15:06,698 --> 00:15:10,154
Not before he conquered the known world.

165
00:15:11,376 --> 00:15:13,238
- Dismissed.
- Yes, sir.

166
00:15:18,148 --> 00:15:21,079
He has a complicated response to authority.

167
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:26,070
He wants to please the overbearing father figure
but resents the lack of reciprocated affection.

168
00:15:26,071 --> 00:15:27,864
His isolation can never be broken

169
00:15:27,865 --> 00:15:31,809
and he must never believe anyone will help him.

170
00:15:32,169 --> 00:15:34,684
Oh look. It's the smartass.

171
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:44,832
Thanks!
Thought I'd have to ask to be by the door.

172
00:15:52,522 --> 00:15:57,339
<i>#State your name.#</i>
- Ender Wiggin.

173
00:16:01,732 --> 00:16:06,852
- Don't freeze your balls, kid.
- Attention on deck.

174
00:16:07,371 --> 00:16:08,942
At ease.

175
00:16:09,222 --> 00:16:11,524
Listen up, Launchies!

176
00:16:11,525 --> 00:16:20,915
My name is Sergeant James Dap. Ask me a
legitimate question and I will give you a direct answer..

177
00:16:20,916 --> 00:16:25,384
but if you are looking for a shoulder
to cry on, use your pillow.

178
00:16:26,046 --> 00:16:30,410
- Do I look like I'm joking, snots?
- Sir! No, sir!

179
00:16:30,411 --> 00:16:33,901
Good.
You are to work as a team..

180
00:16:33,902 --> 00:16:38,823
You will all make this bunkroom, your home.
You will keep your home clean.

181
00:16:38,823 --> 00:16:40,906
There are separate showers for both sexes.

182
00:16:40,907 --> 00:16:44,850
If you are found in an area not designated to your gender,

183
00:16:44,851 --> 00:16:49,728
I will personally neuter you.
- Am I clear?
- Sir! Yes sir!

184
00:16:54,567 --> 00:17:01,271
- Class is in five. Follow the yellow lights.
  Yellow like your cowardly selves.
- Sir! Yes, sir!

185
00:17:01,749 --> 00:17:03,703
Welcome to Battle School.

186
00:17:03,704 --> 00:17:06,868
A great responsibility rests on each of you.

187
00:17:06,869 --> 00:17:09,870
When the enemy first invaded, we were not ready.

188
00:17:09,871 --> 00:17:12,907
Millions of innocent lives were lost.

189
00:17:12,908 --> 00:17:16,188
That must never be allowed to happen again.

190
00:17:16,189 --> 00:17:21,333
We threw everything we had at the invaders.
And in the midst of that decisive battle,

191
00:17:22,915 --> 00:17:25,837
a legendary hero emerged.

192
00:18:20,272 --> 00:18:23,447
We will never forget what the enemy did

193
00:18:23,448 --> 00:18:25,576
but we defeated them.

194
00:18:25,577 --> 00:18:29,174
and we will do so again.

195
00:18:29,628 --> 00:18:35,876
Let the courage of Mazer Rackham
be your inspiration.

196
00:18:36,121 --> 00:18:38,913
Wakey wakey.
Rise and shine.

197
00:18:38,914 --> 00:18:40,658
Put on your Battle Room suits

198
00:18:40,658 --> 00:18:44,148
That's the padded one with the helmet and the weapon.

199
00:18:44,149 --> 00:18:46,977
Do not attempt to fire the weapon.

200
00:18:46,977 --> 00:18:53,260
Holster it! Let's move it launchies, you've got 10 minutes!

201
00:19:00,966 --> 00:19:03,269
At ease!

202
00:19:03,374 --> 00:19:04,805
This is the Battle Room.

203
00:19:04,805 --> 00:19:10,040
In here, the floor's been designed
to create an Earth-like gravitational pull.

204
00:19:10,041 --> 00:19:15,313
Step through that gate
and you are in a zero-G environment.

205
00:19:21,249 --> 00:19:24,559
Wiggin!
Get up here.

206
00:19:52,620 --> 00:19:58,137
- What do I do now, sir?
- Go on in.

207
00:20:15,497 --> 00:20:19,547
Alright now, push off.

208
00:21:14,797 --> 00:21:16,065
Nicely done.

209
00:21:16,065 --> 00:21:19,126
These guys are still trying to
stay up the way they came in.

210
00:21:19,126 --> 00:21:22,546
But like you said in the shuttle,
there is no up or down in space.

211
00:21:22,547 --> 00:21:25,550
But we'll need some way
to orientate in here...

212
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:28,132
...maybe the enemy's gate is down?

213
00:21:28,133 --> 00:21:35,254
- I get it, like they're a bug to be
crushed under our feet.
- Exactly.

214
00:21:38,339 --> 00:21:42,668
- What do you think this does?
- Let's find out.

215
00:21:51,927 --> 00:21:54,396
Whoa! Won't acts harmless... (???)

216
00:21:54,397 --> 00:21:59,774
- What do you think it does when it hits the suit?
- Good question.

217
00:22:05,999 --> 00:22:10,839
- Shoot me in the leg.
- We shoot each other. Same time.

218
00:22:11,412 --> 00:22:13,227
Ready?

219
00:22:20,009 --> 00:22:24,513
- Whoa! My leg's frozen!
- Mine too.

220
00:22:24,861 --> 00:22:26,678
I can't bend my knee...

221
00:22:29,924 --> 00:22:35,299
Shoot me in the chest...
Come on! I'm getting away.

222
00:22:40,535 --> 00:22:46,888
- This is amazing...
  I can't move at all now.
- Out of his mind.

223
00:22:46,889 --> 00:22:48,843
That's enough.

224
00:23:03,587 --> 00:23:06,612
You're flapping around like
a bunch of drunken ducks.

225
00:23:06,638 --> 00:23:10,254
If you expect to compete with the
other teams in this School...

226
00:23:10,255 --> 00:23:15,178
... you've got a lot to learn.
Sergeant, explain the game!
- Yes Sir!

227
00:23:16,423 --> 00:23:20,820
You will train to compete as a team
against other teams.

228
00:23:20,821 --> 00:23:24,268
You get 1 point for a hit to a limb, 
six for a torso hit

229
00:23:24,294 --> 00:23:26,929
- which will immobilize you completely -...

230
00:23:26,930 --> 00:23:32,962
...but if either side gets one cadet
through the enemy's gate unharmed...

231
00:23:32,988 --> 00:23:35,993
...that army will win.
Regardless of points already scored.

232
00:23:35,994 --> 00:23:39,474
- Am I clear?
- Sir! Yes Sir!

233
00:23:39,963 --> 00:23:45,198
Dear Valentine, so this is Battle School...
Every day, hours of training...

234
00:23:45,199 --> 00:23:48,236
...and far more homework
than we ever had on Earth.

235
00:23:48,306 --> 00:23:51,762
We train in hand-to-hand combat...

236
